Stopwatch — Firefox Extension
==============================

A minimal, zero-bloat stopwatch extension for Firefox.
Start, pause, lap, and reset. The timer keeps running in
the background even when the popup is closed.

No storage. No network requests. No tracking.
No external dependencies. No build tools.


Features
--------
  - Start / Pause / Resume
  - Lap tracking with best and worst lap highlighting
  - Delta time per lap
  - Timer runs in background while popup is closed
  - Resets cleanly on browser restart (intentional)
  - Local fonts, zero external requests


Files
-----
  manifest.json   Extension config
  background.js   Keeps timer alive in background
  popup.html      UI
  popup.js        UI logic
  icon-48.png     Toolbar icon (48x48)
  icon-96.png     Toolbar icon (96x96)
  fonts/          Locally bundled fonts (Share Tech Mono, Rajdhani)


Install
-------
  This extension is unlisted and not publicly available
  on the Firefox Add-ons marketplace.

  To install from source:
    1. Download or clone this repo
    2. Go to about:debugging in Firefox
    3. Click "This Firefox" -> "Load Temporary Add-on"
    4. Select manifest.json from the extension folder

  Note: Temporary installs are removed when Firefox closes.
  For a permanent install, submit the zip of the extension
  files to addons.mozilla.org/developers — Mozilla will sign
  it and return a .xpi file you can install permanently via
  about:addons -> gear icon -> Install Add-on From File.
  Alternatively, set xpinstall.signatures.required to false
  in about:config (not recommended for daily use).


Tech
----
  Plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
  No frameworks. No bundler. No minifier.
  Uses browser.runtime messaging between popup and background.
  Timer state lives purely in memory — no storage API used.


